ombine these forms to become “directeur-trice-s”.%0a%3c The Academie stated that it could not see the “desired objective” of the changes (big surprise given the lack of diversity of its membership) and argued that it would complicate writing and speaking too much and put burden on French speakers (as if French wasn’t already unnecessarily complicated). This lack of inclusivity, resistance to evolution of the language, and prescriptivist perspective of gender inclusive language is abhorrent but unfortunately not unexpected from a group with a history of discrimination and no inclination to change. Gender inclusive language does not belong to a dialect of French (that I know of) but nonetheless the lack of acceptance towards equality in the French language is discriminatory against every person that does not identify as male, which is a good 50%25+ of the population. It's embarrassing for France that this group exists. %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:section: C:)%0a%3c (:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
